nt%20in%20name%2C%20in%20its%20beliefs%2C%20it%20remains%20misunderstood%20and%20mischaracterised.%20In%20the%20UK%2C%20Zephaniah%20became%20its%20standard%20bearer.%20His%20public%20adherence%20represented%20a%20full%20frontal%20challenge%20to%20the%20pervasive%20criminal%20stereotypes%20with%20which%20racist%20politicians%20and%20police%20forces%20have%20long%20tagged%20Rastafari.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPersecution%20of%20Rastafari%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EZephaniah%20was%20born%20and%20raised%20in%20the%20Handsworth%20area%20of%20Birmingham%20in%201958.%20He%20came%20of%20age%20in%20the%20late%201970s%2C%20as%20the%20UK%20fell%20head%20first%20into%20Thatcherism%20and%20the%20far-right%20National%20Front%20achieved%20its%20biggest%20ever%20vote%20tally.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBlack%20Rastafari%20of%20the%20era%20invariably%20faced%20daily%20racist%20persecution.%20Faith-based%20persecution%2C%20endorsed%20by%20the%20establishment%2C%20was%20soon%20to%20follow.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flink.springer.com%2Fchapter%2F10.1007%2F978-1-349-19399-8_3%5C%22%3ESociologists%3C%2Fa%3E%20point%20to%20a%201977%20report%20commissioned%20by%20the%20West%20Midlands%20Police%20and%20titled%20Shades%20of%20Grey%20as%20having%20been%20instrumental%20in%20creating%2C%20as%20journalist%20Derek%20Bishton%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fderekbishton.com%2Fshades-of-grey-a-report-on-police-west-indian-relations-in-handsworth%2F%5C%22%3Enotes%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20popular%20sentiment%20that%20Black%20people%20were%20much%20more%20predisposed%20to%20criminality%2C%20and%20that%20it%20was%20their%20culture%20which%20produced%20this%20behaviour%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20insidiously%20associated%20%E2%80%9Chardcore%20Dreadlocks%E2%80%9D%20with%20%E2%80%9Ca%20criminalised%20sub-culture%E2%80%9D.%20It%20asserted%20this%20community%20posed%20a%20constant%20threat%20to%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20peace%20of%20individual%20citizens%